      "lesson title": "AI Risks in Online Travel Platforms",
      "order": 1,
      "Description": "Online travel platforms increasingly rely on artificial intelligence to power everything from price recommendations to customer service chatbots, but this dependence introduces a range of risks that are important to understand. When these platforms draw on third-party systems and external data sources, there is a real possibility that inaccurate or outdated information reaches the traveller, leading to booking errors or unexpected costs. This lesson explores how AI-driven tools can sometimes produce unreliable results, particularly when the underlying data is incomplete or poorly maintained. You will also look at the practical implications for both travellers and travel businesses, including how to spot potential issues and what questions to ask before trusting an AI-generated recommendation. No prior technical knowledge is required, and the focus throughout is on building everyday awareness of how these risks can affect real travel experiences.",
