          "subtitle": "Risks When External Data Sources Fail",
          "slidecontent": "• Online travel platforms rely heavily on external providers like flight databases, hotel APIs, and payment gateways\n\n• When these third-party sources go down or send incorrect data, the AI has no reliable information to work with\n\n• Outdated pricing or availability data can cause the AI to make bookings that are impossible to fulfil\n\n• Data gaps can trigger errors\n\n• Inconsistent data formats across suppliers make it harder for AI systems to interpret and act on information accurately"
